@BookingService_HostAddress = http://localhost:5290

### Everything below requires a real token — register + login via
### AuthService.http first, then paste the resulting token here.
### Use a second, different user's token as @token2 for the
### double-booking/ownership tests below.
@token = PASTE_TOKEN_HERE
@token2 = PASTE_A_DIFFERENT_USERS_TOKEN_HERE

### ============================================================
### Reserve
### ============================================================

### No token at all — expect 401
POST {{BookingService_HostAddress}}/bookings/reserve
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticketIds": ["00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"]
}

### Reserve a ticket — copy a real, currently-Available ticket id from
### GET http://localhost:5049/events/search (Event Service)
POST {{BookingService_HostAddress}}/bookings/reserve
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "ticketIds": ["00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"]
}

### Reserve the SAME ticket again as a DIFFERENT user (token2) — expect 409,
### proves the Redis lock prevents double-booking
POST {{BookingService_HostAddress}}/bookings/reserve
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token2}}

{
  "ticketIds": ["00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"]
}

### ============================================================
### Pay + confirm
### Needs `stripe listen --forward-to localhost:5290/webhooks/stripe`
### running in its own terminal, or the booking never actually
### confirms in our own database (Stripe itself still succeeds either way).
### ============================================================

### Pay for a booking — copy a real bookingId from a successful reserve
### response above. Must be the SAME user (token) who reserved it.
POST {{BookingService_HostAddress}}/bookings/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/pay
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### A DIFFERENT user (token2) tries to pay for someone else's booking —
### expect 403
POST {{BookingService_HostAddress}}/bookings/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/pay
Authorization: Bearer {{token2}}

### Pay again on the same (now-confirmed) booking — expect 400,
### "This booking is already confirmed."
POST {{BookingService_HostAddress}}/bookings/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/pay
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================================
### Virtual waiting queue
### ============================================================

### Turn on queue protection for an event — copy a real eventId from
### GET http://localhost:5049/events/search (Event Service)
POST {{BookingService_HostAddress}}/queue/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/enable
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Join the queue for that event
POST {{BookingService_HostAddress}}/queue/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/join
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Check your own queue status/position
GET {{BookingService_HostAddress}}/queue/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Reserve a ticket for that event BEFORE being admitted — expect 403.
### Wait for the admission cycle (Queue:AdmissionIntervalSeconds in
### appsettings.Development.json, 2 minutes by default) then re-check status
### above and retry this — should now succeed.
POST {{BookingService_HostAddress}}/bookings/reserve
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "ticketIds": ["00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"]
}

###
